{"id":67,"date":"2020-05-20T12:10:26","date_gmt":"2020-05-20T12:10:26","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/cmhammar.skapaweb6.tripnet.se\/?page_id=67"},"modified":"2025-12-18T14:39:13","modified_gmt":"2025-12-18T13:39:13","slug":"lifejacket-inflators","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/lifejacket-inflators\/","title":{"rendered":"Lifejacket Inflators"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<h1>\n\t\t\tlifejacket inflators\t<\/h1>\n\t<p>The inflator gives your inflatable lifejacket its buoyancy that is vital for your lifejacket&#8217;s performance. One might say it is the heart of the inflatable lifejacket.<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/plugins\/bb-plugin\/img\/pixel.png\" alt=\"\" itemprop=\"image\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 3px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 3\/2;\" \/>\n<h3>\n\t\t\tOPTIMIZED FOR ROUGH CONDITIONS\t<\/h3>\n\t<p>Despite its small size, the inflator is of huge importance for your lifejacket&#8217;s performance. The inflator&#8217;s mission is to give your lifejacket full buoyancy when you need it.<\/p>\n<p>Hammar&#8217;s Lifejacket Inflators are designed to activate only when needed and prevent accidental activations. Whether activated automatically or manually, we believe an inflator <i>optimized for rough conditions<\/i> is a <b>Better Solution for Safety at Sea<\/b>.<\/p>\n<h3>\n\t\t\tWHAT IS AN INFLATABLE LIFEJACKET?\t<\/h3>\n\t<p>Lifejackets have saved lives at sea for decades by giving a person in the water the extra buoyancy to stay afloat. You may either wear a lifejacket where the needed displacement element is at all-time present. Or, you may have a lifejacket that creates extra buoyancy by inflating a bladder using compressed gas, a so called inflatable lifejacket.\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>The inflator initiates the release of compressed gas, either automatically in water or manually, by pulling a handle. Inflatable lifejackets are the primary choice for users requiring better mobility and high flotation due to worn gear and the state of the sea.<\/p>\n<p>Inflatable lifejackets are considered personal safety equipment and should be serviced and controlled regularly.<\/p>\n\t<a href=\"#modal276070219\" data-toggle=\"modal\">\n    Lifejacket Standards      <\/a>\n                                <p>Lifejackets have many names depending on the country, intended area of use, and approval standard. Here are some examples: PFD (Personal Flotation Device), LPU (Life Preserving Unit), Life Preserver, Life Vest, or even Mae West.Different lifejackets are suitable for different conditions and areas at sea, and there are different standards for levels of use. Inflatable jackets are primarily used in more demanding applications as they allow a lifejacket with high buoyancy (&gt;150N) to be compact, slim, and more comfortable to wear. Inflatable lifejackets with high buoyancy (&gt;150N) also often allow for the displacement to be positioned favorably for turning a person face up and floating high in the water.<h2>Standards for lifejackets<\/h2>There are several different organizations setting standards for lifejackets. Depending on the area of use, the correct standard should be chosen. Here are some of the more common standards:<h3><b>ISO lifejacket standards<\/b><\/h3>The <a href=\"https:\/\/www.iso.org\/home.html\">ISO<\/a> defines Personal Flotation Devices (PFD) in ISO 12402. The standard is commonly recognized and used by many manufacturers. It consists of four Performance Levels (PL):<ul><li aria-level=\"1\"><b>PL 275 (ISO 12402-2:2020).<\/b> Provides at least 275N of buoyancy for offshore use in severe conditions when protective clothing is being used, or when additional loads are being carried. The lifejacket should provide high flotation and be able to turn an unconscious person to face up.\u00a0<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\"><b>PL 150 (ISO 12402-3:2020). <\/b>Provides at least 150N of buoyancy for offshore or rough water use, or when the users are fully clothed. This is the most common flotation level, often designed so that an unconscious person will turn face up.<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\"><b>PL 100 (ISO 12402-4:2020).<\/b> Provides at least 100N of buoyancy for use in sheltered or calm water, or when the users are fully clothed.<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\"><b>PL 50 (ISO 12402-5:2020).<\/b> Provides at least 50N of buoyancy for use in sheltered waters. This level is usually called buoyancy aid.<\/li><\/ul><h3><b>SOLAS lifejacket standards<\/b><\/h3>The <a href=\"https:\/\/www.imo.org\/\">IMO<\/a> also defines standards for inflatable lifejackets under the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.imo.org\/en\/About\/Conventions\/Pages\/International-Convention-for-the-Safety-of-Life-at-Sea-(SOLAS),-1974.aspx\">SOLAS<\/a> regulation. SOLAS is for commercial users and applies in vessels of more than 500 gross tonnage.The IMO resolution 48(66) set the functional requirements for a SOLAS-approved lifejacket. The European Union has adopted and approved these standards under the Marine Equipment Directive (MED). The latest directive was introduced in July 2010.<\/p>                              \n\t\t<meta itemprop=\"url\" content=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Inflatabel-Lifejacket-in-action.mp4\" \/><div style=\"width: 640px;\" class=\"wp-video\"><video muted class=\"wp-video-shortcode\" id=\"video-67-1\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" loop autoplay preload=\"metadata\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"video\/mp4\" src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Inflatabel-Lifejacket-in-action.mp4?_=1\" \/><source type=\"video\/mp4\" src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Inflatabel-Lifejacket-in-action.mp4?_=1\" \/><a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Inflatabel-Lifejacket-in-action.mp4\">https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Inflatabel-Lifejacket-in-action.mp4<\/a><\/video><\/div>\t\n\t\t<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/_wBnxa3NDHA\" title=\"YouTube video player\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" data-load-mode=\"1\"><\/iframe>\t\n<h3>\n\t\t\tWHAT DOES AN INFLATOR DO?\t<\/h3>\n\t<p>The inflator is where the energy for puncturing the gas cylinder is stored or generated. An automatic inflator will commonly store the energy needed in a spring under tension held by a water-sensitive element. The element will break at entry into the water, releasing the spring connected to a pin, piercing the cylinder, and releasing gas into the bladder. The bladder increases in volume and creates buoyancy. A manual activation either releases the energy or generates the force needed to puncture the cylinder with the pull of the handle.<\/p>\n<h3>\n\t\t\tTECHNOLOGIES\t<\/h3>\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/IA-0505_image_09_Crop.png\" alt=\"IA-0505_image_09_Crop\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"1253\" width=\"1253\" title=\"IA-0505_image_09_Crop\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 1253px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 1253\/1253;\" \/>\n<h3>\n\t\t\tAUTOMATIC ACTIVATION WITH HYDROSTATIC TECHNOLOGY\t<\/h3>\n\t<p>Hammar&#8217;s Lifejacket Inflators are equipped with hydrostatic protection and use a valve to protect the water-sensitive element that gives exceptional protection against accidental inflation in the case of rain, spray, splash, or humidity. When the inflators are exposed to sufficient pressure, they will open their hydrostatic valve, allowing the water to meet the water-sensitive element and start the activation.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/lifejacket-inflators\/#ma1-technology\">Learn more<\/a><\/p>\n\t<a href=\"#modal697195205\" data-toggle=\"modal\">\n    Inflators with Automatic Activation      <\/a>\n                                <p>Hammar&#8217;s range of automatic inflators uses hydrostatic technology to prevent accidental activation. The water-sensitive element holding a wound-up spring is protected behind a hydrostatic valve, which opens at around ten centimeters of water pressure.All Hammar Lifejacket Inflators share the same interface with the lifejacket bladder (the sealing ring) but differ in the type of piercing mechanism used. The Hammar MA1 and Hammar M2 are compatible and use the same model piercing mechanism.<h3>MA1 AUTOMATIC\/MANUAL INFLATOR<\/h3><a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/IA-0600.png\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/IA-0600.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"1000\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 1000px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 1000\/1000;\" \/><\/a>The Hammar MA1 is the second generation of automatic inflators from Hammar designed to match both <a href=\"https:\/\/www.uscg.mil\/\">USCG<\/a> and the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.iso.org\/home.html\">ISO<\/a> standards.<ul><li aria-level=\"1\">The MA1 is highly resistant to rain, sea, and swell with hydrostatic technology.<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">It is approved towards the highest humidity resistance standards of the USCG.<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">No service of the inflator cap is required for five years.<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">The single point indicator, the green indicator for &#8220;OK to use,&#8221; and expiry date are located within a small radius to check inflator status easily.<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">The MA1 has a protected gas cylinder permanently fixed to the piercing unit, making unwinding of the cylinder impossible.<\/li><\/ul><a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/5-year-lifetime-black.png\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/5-year-lifetime-black-150x150.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100\" height=\"102\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 100px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 100\/102;\" \/><\/a> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/cylinder-sealed-protected-black.png\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/cylinder-sealed-protected-black-150x150.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 100px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 100\/100;\" \/><\/a> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/humidity-resistance-black.png\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/humidity-resistance-black-150x150.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"101\" height=\"101\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 101px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 101\/101;\" \/><\/a> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/rain-and-wave-resistance-black.png\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/rain-and-wave-resistance-black-150x150.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"99\" height=\"99\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 99px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 99\/99;\" \/><\/a> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/single-point-indication-black.png\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/single-point-indication-black-150x150.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 100px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 100\/100;\" \/><\/a> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/temperature-black.png\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/temperature-black-150x150.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"98\" height=\"98\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 98px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 98\/98;\" \/><\/a>The MA1 comes in a variety of manual pull cord lengths. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/product-category\/lifejacket-inflators\/ma1-ec\/\">Here you can find the options available.<\/a><h3>A1 AUTOMATIC\/MANUAL INFLATOR<\/h3><a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/IA-0400.png\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/IA-0400.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"1000\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 1000px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 1000\/1000;\" \/><\/a>The automatic Hammar inflator A1 is the first generation of our Hydrostatic Inflator System used on older EN-approved lifejackets. Today&#8217;s successor is our <a href=\"https:\/\/www.iso.org\/home.html\">ISO-approved<\/a> MA1 model.<ul><li aria-level=\"1\">The A1 has the same unique hydrostatic valve and protection against unintentional activation as the MA1 model.<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">No service of the inflator cap is required for five years.<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">There is no single point indicator, so the gas cylinder has to be manually checked.<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">The A1 has a protected gas cylinder.<\/li><\/ul><a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/5-year-lifetime-black.png\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/5-year-lifetime-black-150x150.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100\" height=\"102\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 100px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 100\/102;\" \/><\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/humidity-resistance-black.png\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/humidity-resistance-black-150x150.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"101\" height=\"101\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 101px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 101\/101;\" \/><\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/rain-and-wave-resistance-black.png\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/rain-and-wave-resistance-black-150x150.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"99\" height=\"99\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 99px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 99\/99;\" \/><\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/temperature-black.png\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/temperature-black-150x150.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"98\" height=\"98\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 98px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 98\/98;\" \/><\/a><i>The A1 uses the same interface with the lifejacket as the MA1 model. But if you want to use the MA1 model on an EN-approved lifejacket, you must check with the manufacturer if that particular lifejacket is approved with the MA1 model.<\/i><\/p>                              \n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/IM-6125_image_01_Crop2.png\" alt=\"IM-6125_image_01_Crop2\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"927\" width=\"927\" title=\"IM-6125_image_01_Crop2\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 927px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 927\/927;\" \/>\n<h3>\n\t\t\tMANUAL ACTIVATION\t<\/h3>\n\t<p>Activate the inflator manually by using the pull-tab, and the lifejacket will reach full buoyancy within seconds. The manual pull creates the necessary force to make the piercing pin puncture the cylinder and return to its original position for a free gas flow into the bladder.\u00a0The inflator is designed to ensure fast and reliable activation when you need it. You should don the lifejacket according to the manufacturer&#8217;s instructions to secure the lifejacket&#8217;s function.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\t<a href=\"#modal1897872796\" data-toggle=\"modal\">\n    Inflators with Manual Activation      <\/a>\n                                <h3>M2 MANUAL INFLATOR<\/h3><p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/M2.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/M2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"384\" height=\"928\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 384px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 384\/928;\" \/><\/a>The Hammar M2 is a manual inflator meaning it will only activate by pulling the handle. The M2 is the second generation of manual inflators from Hammar. It is compatible with the MA1 piercing unit.\u00a0<ul><li aria-level=\"1\">The M2 has a single point indicator.<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">The inflator cap has a five-year expiry date.<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">The M2 has a protected gas cylinder, permanently fixed to the piercing mechanism and protected from corrosion with its position inside the bladder.<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">It has a slim design and is light in weight.<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">The M2 is compatible to upgrade with the MA1.<\/li><\/ul><a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/5-year-lifetime-black.png\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/5-year-lifetime-black-150x150.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100\" height=\"102\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 100px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 100\/102;\" \/><\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/cylinder-sealed-protected-black.png\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/cylinder-sealed-protected-black-150x150.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 100px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 100\/100;\" \/><\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/single-point-indication-black.png\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/single-point-indication-black-150x150.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 100px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 100\/100;\" \/><\/a>\u00a0<h3>M1 MANUAL INFLATOR<\/h3><a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/IM-0400.png\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/IM-0400.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"1000\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 1000px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 1000\/1000;\" \/><\/a>The manual Hammar inflator M1 is only for manual activation and is activated by pulling the red handle. The gas cylinder is punctured with a needle, and the lifejacket inflates within seconds.<\/p><ul><li aria-level=\"1\">The M1 only needs replacement after use.<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">There is no expiry date on the inflator cap.<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">The M1 has a protected gas cylinder.<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">It is small and light in weight.<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">The M1 is compatible to upgrade from an M1 to an A1.<\/li><\/ul>                              \n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Hammar-COR-003.jpg\" alt=\"Hammar COR (003)\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"1004\" width=\"1322\" title=\"Hammar COR (003)\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 1322px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 1322\/1004;\" \/>\n<h3>\n\t\t\tPRECISION AND CONTROL USING ELECTRONIC CONTROL UNIT\t<\/h3>\n\t<p>The Hammar COR Electronic Inflator System is a new patented technology. It can be customized to specific requirements and optimized for different applications. The technology creates a rapid and reliable activation of the PFD (Personal Flotation Devices) even under extreme conditions.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/lifejacket-inflators\/#cor-technology\">Learn more<\/a><\/p>\n\t<a href=\"#modal167088978\" data-toggle=\"modal\">\n    Models with Electronic Activation      <\/a>\n\t\t\t\t                          <h2>COR<\/h2>\n                                <p><b>COR technology<\/b>The COR technology allows for seven different activation modes based on four parameters: Pressure, submersion time, presence of water, and temperature. The mode is specified to the manufacturer&#8217;s specification, and the model of COR is unique to your lifejacket.<\/p>                              \n <h3>\n\t\t\tOPTIMIZED FOR ROUGH CONDITIONS\t<\/h3>\n\t<p>Heavy rain will not activate it. Large unexpected waves will not activate it. Extreme humidity, or even being exposed to the pressure in an airplane-cabin, will not activate it.<\/p>\n<h3>\n\t\t\tHYDROSTATIC TECHNOLOGY\t<\/h3>\n\t<p>Hammar&#8217;s Lifejacket Inflators are equipped with a hydrostatic valve that gives exceptional protection against accidental inflation in the case of rain, spray, splash, or humidity. When the inflator is exposed to sufficient differential pressure, the hydrostatic valve will open, allowing the water to meet the water-sensitive element and start the activation.<\/p>\n<p>It is important to don the lifejacket according to the manufacturer&#8217;s instructions to secure the function of the lifejacket and automatic inflation.<\/p>\n\t<a href=\"#modal641132776\" data-toggle=\"modal\">\n    Learn more      <\/a>\n                                <p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/inflator_iwperf_light_750px.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/inflator_iwperf_light_750px.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"233\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 750px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 750\/233;\" \/><\/a>The Hammar Lifejacket Inflator automatically activates when submerged, and there is a pressure difference of about ten centimeters. The lifejacket will reach full buoyancy within seconds, and it is designed to ensure fast and reliable activation, only when needed, even in the most extreme weather conditions.<ul><li aria-level=\"1\">If you fall into the water face down, the lifejacket will inflate automatically. It will also turn you around, so your head gets out of the water.<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">If you fall into the water and the inflator does not reach a water depth of ten centimeters:<ul><li aria-level=\"2\">You will float anyway. However, if you still want the lifevest to inflate, you can easily inflate the lifejacket manually with the pull-tab.<\/li><li aria-level=\"2\">You will float anyway and can have more latitude swimming to safety.<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/hydrostatic-valve.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/hydrostatic-valve.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"588\" height=\"584\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 588px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 588\/584;\" \/><\/a><h3>Measuring the pressure<\/h3>The automatic inflator consists of a hydrostatic valve, a water-sensitive element holding a spring, and a gas cylinder. When the inflator is exposed to sufficient differential pressure, it will open its hydrostatic valve, allowing the water to meet the water-sensitive element and start the activation.The differential pressure is the difference between the air pressure inside the bladder and the water pressure outside the bladder. Therefore, air inside must be limited to a minimum and free to move to the bladder&#8217;s highest point.The inflator uses the pressure difference between the internal and external pressure of the inflator. The water depth of the inflator determines the external pressure, while the trapped air bubble in the lifejacket bladder determines the internal pressure. There is always some air left, even in a well-vacuumed lifejacket bladder.When the lifejacket enters the water, the air bubble inside the bladder will move to the highest point of the bladder. If some part of the lifejacket is above the water, the air bubble will move to that area. If the whole lifejacket is submerged, the air bubble will move to the highest point closest to the surface.The pressure difference is determined by the depth of the inflator and the highest point where the trapped air bubbles have gathered. If this distance is more than ten centimeters, the inflator will activate, and the lifejacket inflates.<a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Pressure-difference.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Pressure-difference.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"646\" height=\"312\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 646px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 646\/312;\" \/><\/a><\/p>                              \n\t\t<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/f8gZrWKrfNY\" title=\"YouTube video player\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" data-load-mode=\"1\"><\/iframe>\t\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/bb-plugin\/cache\/5-year-lifetime-black-circle-fff901c09838c36d75055085204d5193-.png\" alt=\"rwrwrwrqrqrqwrqwafasfdaDDASCASDFAWDAWDASDS\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"3696\" width=\"3696\" title=\"rwrwrwrqrqrqwrqwafasfdaDDASCASDFAWDAWDASDS\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 3696px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 3696\/3696;\" \/>\n<h2>5 year lifetime<\/h2><p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>The Hammar Lifejacket Inflator needs no service or maintenance. Just make sure to replace the inflator after the five-year expiry date or when the single point indicator is red.<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/bb-plugin\/cache\/cylinder-sealed-protected-black-circle-64e64f7ce20494ab4fdb1c956c2f245d-.png\" alt=\"\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"3696\" width=\"3696\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 3696px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 3696\/3696;\" \/>\n<h2>Protected cylinder seal<\/h2><p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>The gas cylinder is placed inside the inflatable bladder and therefore protected from the atmosphere and corrosive effects of saltwater, and reduces snagging hazards. The cylinder is permanently fixed to the piercing unit, making it impossible to unwind the cylinder.<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/bb-plugin\/cache\/humidity-resistance-black-circle-a027f0742c8f909c76f8a1b9c6b3c72a-.png\" alt=\"\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"3696\" width=\"3696\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 3696px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 3696\/3696;\" \/>\n<h2>Humidity resistance<\/h2><p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>The Hammar Lifejacket Inflator is equipped with a hydrostatic valve that gives exceptional protection against accidental inflation in the case of humidity. The inflator passes the highest standard in a humid atmosphere when tested by the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.uscg.mil\/\">USCG<\/a>.<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/bb-plugin\/cache\/rain-and-wave-resistance-black-circle-d03079e3fcb517bf6fb3d74b00798c82-.png\" alt=\"\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"3696\" width=\"3696\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 3696px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 3696\/3696;\" \/>\n<h2>Rain &#038; wave resistance<\/h2><p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>The Hammar Lifejacket Inflator is equipped with a hydrostatic valve that gives exceptional protection against accidental inflation in the case of rain, spray, and splash.<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/bb-plugin\/cache\/single-point-indication-black-circle-b5105a1bfb023a0db27df3806054d06a-.png\" alt=\"\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"3696\" width=\"3696\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 3696px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 3696\/3696;\" \/>\n<h2>Single point indication<\/h2><p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>You will find all information needed to determine your inflator&#8217;s status, single point indication, and expiry date close together. When the single point indicator is green, the inflator is ready for use. After activation (automatic or manual), the indicator turns red, and the inflator needs to be replaced.<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/bb-plugin\/cache\/temperature-black-circle-88ef929297d46501a6f1f0a7cbbf4f3b-.png\" alt=\"\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"3696\" width=\"3696\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 3696px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 3696\/3696;\" \/>\n<h2>Low temperature<\/h2><p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>The Hammar Inflator Systems are suitable to operate in cold conditions due to the cylinder location inside the bladder, and moisture cannot get in to form ice. Furthermore, the CO2 does not have to enter through a valve to inflate the lifejacket. This minimizes the risk of icing during inflation.<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/h-black_on_yellow_01.jpg\" alt=\"Print\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"1808\" width=\"1800\" title=\"Print\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 1800px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 1800\/1808;\" \/>\n\t\t<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/AGRYpUCjxCw\" title=\"YouTube video player\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" data-load-mode=\"1\"><\/iframe>\t\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/COR_in_Water_001.png\" alt=\"COR_in_Water_001\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"1000\" width=\"1000\" title=\"COR_in_Water_001\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 1000px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 1000\/1000;\" \/>\n<h3>\n\t\t\tCOR TECHNOLOGY\t<\/h3>\n\t<p>The patented Hammar COR technology uses an electric signal to ignite a small explosive charge to give the lifejacket full buoyancy when the activation conditions are met.<\/p>\n<p>The small charge makes an efficient piercing in the cylinder with little gas restrictions, which increases the flow of gas to the buoyancy chamber. The method also provides superior reliability in cold condition inflations and minimizes the risk of icing.<\/p>\n<p>The parameters for activation are predefined and customized to meet the users&#8217; demands. Hammar&#8217;s ECU (Electronic Control Unit) can be programmed with up to seven operating modes.\u00a0<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/special-applications\/#cor-applications\">Hammar COR technology, used in other applications.<\/a><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\t<a href=\"#modal2013705167\" data-toggle=\"modal\">\n    Learn more      <\/a>\n                                <h3>Patented Cylinder Piercing<a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/210208COR-Piercing.png\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/210208COR-Piercing.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 1280px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 1280\/720;\" \/><\/a><\/h3><p>With the COR&#8217;s patented piercing method leaves no obstructions for the gas coming out of the cylinder, meaning a free and fast gas flow. With no obstructions to the gas flow, cold inflation is exceptional.A small amount of explosive compound is used to blast a hole in the cylinder. The Cylinder Assembly&#8217;s construction allows transportation, storage, and use without any restrictions other than those applied to compressed gases.<h2>Electronic Control Unit (ECU)<\/h2>The parameters for activation are predefined and customized to meet the users&#8217; demands. The ECU can be programmed with up to up to seven different operating modes. The operator selects the preferable mode by using the mode selector in front of the ECU.<h2>Activating Parameters<\/h2>The operating modes are customized and programmed at delivery from Hammar based on the combination of parameters:\u00a0<ul><li aria-level=\"1\">Submersion time at a specified water depth<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">Water pressure (depth)<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">Presence of water<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">Temperature<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">Manual activation only by the pull tab<\/li><\/ul>The above parameters can be combined to create different operating modes to meet precise requirements and applications.The COR Electronic Inflator System can be used in applications operating in rough environments when flexible parameters for activation of cylinders are required.<b>Example of activation mode:<\/b><ol><li aria-level=\"1\">Auto at &gt; 1 meter depth, or by the manual pull tab<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">Auto at &gt; 10 centimeters depth after 10 seconds or 2 meters depth or manual pull tab<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">Auto at &gt;3 meters after 5 seconds or the manual pull tab<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">Manual pull tab only<\/li><\/ol>\u00a0 <a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/l\u00e4ge-1-4.png\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/l\u00e4ge-1-4.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"2064\" height=\"980\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 2064px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 2064\/980;\" \/><\/a>\u00a0<\/p><h3>Features of the COR inflator<\/h3><ul><li aria-level=\"1\">Electronically defined activation<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">Waterproof down to ten meters depth<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">High inflation speed in all temperatures<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">Battery life, four years.<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">Product life is ten years on the ECU and five years on the Cylinder Assembly<br \/><\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">High inflation speed with the patented technology in the Cylinder Assembly.<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">Hammar Sealing Ring interface with bladder (same as MA1, M2, A1, and M1)<\/li><\/ul>                              \n <h3>\n\t\t\tONE SOLUTION INTERFACE\t<\/h3>\n\t<p>The Hammar Lifejacket Inflators integrate with the lifejacket bladder through the sealing ring. Depending on the approval and certification of the lifejacket, the inflator is fully interchangeable with electronic, automatic, or manual inflators. The actual activating mechanism consists of two parts:<\/p>\n\t<a href=\"#modal802821504\" data-toggle=\"modal\">\n    Activating Mechanism      <\/a>\n\t\t\t\t                          <h2>ACTIVATING MECHANISM <\/h2>\n                                <a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/10\/cat_img_IA-0600-380x380-1.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/10\/cat_img_IA-0600-380x380-1-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"IA-0600\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 150px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 150\/150;\" \/><\/a> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/06\/cat_img_IA-0400-500x500-1.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/06\/cat_img_IA-0400-500x500-1-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"IA-0400\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 150px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 150\/150;\" \/><\/a> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/cat_img_IM-0400-500x500-1.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/cat_img_IM-0400-500x500-1-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 150px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 150\/150;\" \/><\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/IM-6125.png\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/IM-6125-300x300.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 150px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 150\/150;\" \/><\/a><p>The activating mechanism, formally known as &#8220;cap&#8221;, is the first of two parts in the Hammar Inflation Systems for inflatable lifejackets. The cap is the front part of the system where the energy and activating mechanism is located, for manual or automatic activation, depending on the model. When the cap is activated, it transfers force to the piercing mechanism, formally known as &#8220;body&#8221; with a cylinder that releases CO2 gas into the lifejacket bladder. The increased volume of the bladder increases the buoyancy of the lifejacket, preventing the person in the water from drowning.\u00a0The activating mechanism uses different technologies: Automatic hydrostatic, manual, or electrical. All mechanisms can be activated manually b\u00fd the pull of a handle.<ul><li aria-level=\"1\"><b>Automatic hydrostatic activating mechanisms<\/b> use a rolled-up spring for storing the force to be delivered to the piercing mechanism. The spring is tensioned by two arms held together by a paper-element. As water enters the inflator, the paper breaks, the arms release, and the coil transfers its energy to the piercing unit. The manual activation caused by the pull in the manual release handle will break the paper and proceed the same path as an automatic activation.\u00a0<\/li><\/ul><ul><li aria-level=\"1\"><b>Manual activating mechanisms<\/b> create a rotational force as the manual release handle is pulled. The force is transferred through the shaft to the piercing mechanism.<\/li><\/ul><b>Electrical activating mechanisms<\/b> use several sensors to determine when to activate. Read more about our <a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/lifejacket-inflators\/#cor-technology\">COR Electronic Inflation System here.<\/a><\/p>                              \n\t<a href=\"#modal1767130043\" data-toggle=\"modal\">\n    Piercing Mechanism      <\/a>\n\t\t\t\t                          <h2>CYLINDER AND PIERCING MECHANISM <\/h2>\n                                <p>The piercing mechanism, formally known as &#8220;body&#8221; with a cylinder, is the second of two parts in the Hammar Inflation Systems for inflatable lifejackets. The body contains the means for piercing the cylinder to release CO2 gas into the lifejacket bladder. The increased volume of the bladder increases the buoyancy of the lifejacket, preventing the person in the water from drowning.<img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/IB-0600-33.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"1000\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 1000px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 1000\/1000;\" \/>The Automatic and Manual Inflator Systems use a sharp pin that is mounted on an eccentric axle. When the rotating force from the activating mechanism is applied to the eccentric axle, the pin will penetrate the gas cylinder and return to its original position. Leaving a distinct hole and plenty of space provides a fast activation and allows for the cool gas to pass. This minimizes the risk of ice crystals forming and blocking the gas&#8217; path and is important, especially in cold climates.Tests show that Hammar&#8217;s piercing mechanism is superior in cold weather activation.The COR Electronic Inflator System uses a brand new patented method for cylinder piercing. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/lifejacket-inflators\/#cor-technology\">Read more about the COR piercing technology here<\/a><h2>Protected gas cylinder<\/h2>The gas cylinder is placed inside the inflatable bladder. This protects it from the atmosphere, corrosive effects of saltwater, and reduces snagging hazards. Extreme cold conditions will not affect the hydrostatic system and moisture cannot enter to form ice crystals. Furthermore, the CO2 does not have to enter through a valve to inflate the lifejacket, which also minimizes the risk of ice crystals forming.On the Hammar MA1 and Hammar M2 piercing mechanism, the cylinder is permanently fixed to prevent unwinding.<a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/cylinder-sealed-protected-scaled.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/cylinder-sealed-protected-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"Cylinder sealed and protected\" width=\"160\" height=\"185\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 160px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 160\/185;\" \/><\/a><\/p>                              \n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/Bildsealing-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"Bildsealing\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"988\" width=\"1800\" title=\"Bildsealing\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 1800px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 1800\/988;\" \/>\n<h3>\n\t\t\tFOR USERS WHO DEMAND SUPERIOR EQUIPMENT\t<\/h3>\n\t<p>Whether you are a fisherman, offshore-sailor, or yachtsman, having an inflatable lifejacket that activates when not needed will lead to complications. The Hammar Lifejacket Inflators are optimized for rough conditions and set to activate only when you need it.<\/p>\n<p>The performance of Hammar&#8217;s automatic inflators in water is its primary function. But you can also rely on the inflator to perform as expected on dry land or when you are exposed to rough conditions. (However, when boarding an airplane, you should always check with your airline if they allow inflatable lifejackets onboard.)<\/p>\n<p>The construction of a lifejacket equipped with a Hammar Automatic Inflator System provides flexibility and more latitude when doing your duties at the boat &#8211; regardless of whether you are out sailing during the weekend or competing in a worldwide ocean race.<\/p>\n\t\t<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/7srfJ_lL3Xs\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" data-load-mode=\"1\"><\/iframe>\t\n<h3>\n\t\t\tTHE WORLDS LEADING LIFEJACKET MANUFACTURERS USE HAMMAR\t<\/h3>\n\t\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row lifejacket-random\">\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n        \r\n            <div class=\"col-md-3 col-sm-4 mt-2 mx-auto\">\r\n                <div class=\"card border p-1\">\r\n                    <a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/lifejacket\/helly-hansen-sailsafe-inflatable-race-170n\/\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/10\/HH-Sailsafe-170N-_front.jpg\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 1984px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 1984\/1994;\"><\/a>                <\/div>\r\n            <\/div>  \r\n \r\n\r\n \r\n        \r\n            <div class=\"col-md-3 col-sm-4 mt-2 mx-auto\">\r\n                <div class=\"card border p-1\">\r\n                    <a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/lifejacket\/mustang-uscg-sar-vest\/\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/10\/Mustang-USCG-SAR-scaled.jpg\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 1800px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 1800\/1800;\"><\/a>                <\/div>\r\n            <\/div>  \r\n \r\n\r\n \r\n        \r\n            <div class=\"col-md-3 col-sm-4 mt-2 mx-auto\">\r\n                <div class=\"card border p-1\">\r\n                    <a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/lifejacket\/seago-active\/\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/10\/SeaGo-Active-190-I-300_front2.jpg\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 2000px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 2000\/2000;\"><\/a>                <\/div>\r\n            <\/div>  \r\n \r\n\r\n \r\n        \r\n            <div class=\"col-md-3 col-sm-4 mt-2 mx-auto\">\r\n                <div class=\"card border p-1\">\r\n                    <a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/lifejacket\/9326\/\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Ursuit-DSH-275N-scaled.jpg\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 1800px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 1800\/1800;\"><\/a>                <\/div>\r\n            <\/div>  \r\n \r\n<\/div>\n\t\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/lifejacket\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tVisit our Lifejacket Showroom\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/a>\n<h3>\n\t\t\tCARE AND SUPPORT FOR YOUR HAMMAR INFLATOR\t<\/h3>\n\t<p>Your Hammar Lifejacket Inflator requires no annual service and only needs replacement of the activation mechanism at expiry. Every time you use your Hammar-equipped lifejacket, check that the single point indicator is green and the year marked on the unit has not passed.<\/p>\n\t\t<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/eF-HaZT5x6E\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" data-load-mode=\"1\"><\/iframe>\t\n<h3>\n\t\t\tHOW DO I REARM MY HAMMAR INFLATOR?\t<\/h3>\n\t<p>If your indicator is red or the year marked on the inflator has passed, you need to rearm your lifejacket. For instructions on how to replace the inflator, please watch the video.<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\"  id=\"fl-accordion--label-0\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-controls=\"fl-accordion--panel-0\">MA1 \/ M2 Rearming Instructions<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\" id=\"fl-accordion--icon-0\"  tabindex=\"0\"><i title=\"Expand\">Expand<\/i><\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<h2>BEFORE YOU START REARMING<\/h2>\n<p>Make sure you have a smooth, flat, and dry work surface.<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Insert the opening key between the black locking ring and the yellow cap. Turn the key anticlockwise. The black locking ring will now turn anticlockwise.<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Hold the yellow cap with one hand and continue to turn the black locking ring anticlockwise with the other hand until it stops.<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Lift the yellow cap. Remove the old inflator body and gas cylinder from inside the bladder and dispose of it in an environmentally friendly manner.<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Check the Rearming Kit. Ensure that all the following four points are met before you continue.<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">\u2022 The single point indicator on the inflator cap is green. ( )<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">\u2022 The indicator on the black body is green. ( )<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">\u2022 The expiry date on the inflator cap is within the limit.<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">\u2022 The size of the gas cylinder is correct.<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Do not assemble any cap or body that does not meet these requirements.<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Insert the inflator body with the gas cylinder pointing upwards in the bladder. Let the sealing ring rest on the rounded sealing surface on the body.<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Position the replacement cap with the hydrostatic valve pointing to the right, 90\u00b0 relative to the gas cylinder, and put the cap in place on the body.<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Press firmly on the inflator cap and turn the black locking ring clockwise into the locked position.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<h2>FINAL CHECK<\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Pull the cap to make sure it has locked on the inflator body properly.<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Check that the locking ring is properly locked and cannot be turned anticlockwise by hand.<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Inflate the lifejacket through the oral tube. Check that it stays inflated at least overnight.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2>PACKING<\/h2>\n<p>Before packing, deflate the lifejacket through the oral tube. Make sure all residual air is pressed out from the bladder to assure the best activating conditions for the inflator and that it can be folded properly according to the manufacturer&#8217;s instruction. Make sure that the lifejacket is dry before packing.<\/p>\n<h3>MAKING THE INFLATOR OPERATIONAL AFTER USE OR WHEN EXPIRED<\/h3>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/rearming-instructions_001.png\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/rearming-instructions_001-300x273.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"541\" height=\"395\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 541px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 541\/395;\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\"  id=\"fl-accordion--label-1\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-controls=\"fl-accordion--panel-1\">MA1 \/ M2 Periodic Service<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\" id=\"fl-accordion--icon-1\"  tabindex=\"0\"><i title=\"Expand\">Expand<\/i><\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<h2>Check Periodically<\/h2>\n<ol>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Check that the single point indicator on the inflator cap is green. ( \u2022 )<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Check that the expiry date on the inflator cap is within the limit.<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Always inspect the sealing ring for wear and tear that can affect the sealing function. Pull the cap and locking ring to make sure it has locked on the inflator body properly.<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Inflate the Hammar MA1 lifejacket through the oral tube. Check that it stays inflated at least overnight.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<h2>Packing<\/h2>\n<p>Before packing, deflate the lifejacket through the oral tube. Make sure all residual air is pressed out from the bladder so that it can be folded properly according to the manufacturer&#8217;s instruction. Make sure the lifejacket is dry before packing.<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\"  id=\"fl-accordion--label-2\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-controls=\"fl-accordion--panel-2\">A1 \/ M1 Rearming Instructions<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\" id=\"fl-accordion--icon-2\"  tabindex=\"0\"><i title=\"Expand\">Expand<\/i><\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<h2>How to rearm an A1\/M1 lifejacket<\/h2>\n<p>Before you start rearming your lifejacket, be sure to have a flat, smooth, and dry work surface.<\/p>\n<p>1. Use the opening key, and insert it between the black locking ring and the yellow cap. Then turn the key counterclockwise. Now, the black locking ring will turn counterclockwise.<\/p>\n<p>2. Continue to turn the black locking ring counterclockwise until it stops. Hold the yellow cap with one hand and the black locking ring with the other hand.<\/p>\n<p>3. You can now lift off the yellow cap. From inside the bladder, remove the used gas cylinder. Be sure to dispose of it in an environmentally friendly manner.<\/p>\n<p>4. Reset the piercing pin by rotating the shaft in the inner body to a position where the underside monitor with an eyelet surrounds the green dot ( \u2022 ) in the center of the indicator.<\/p>\n<p>5. Carefully examine the top of the new gas cylinder to make sure it is not punctured. The cylinder must be very firmly tightened into the black inner body. The black inner body should be checked for any damage or splitting following this tightening.<\/p>\n<p>6. Check your Hammar A1\/M1 Rearming Kit. Ensure that all conditions are met before you continue.<\/p>\n<p><b>Hammar A1 Model:<\/b><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Check that the indicator is green ( \u2022 ).<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Check that the expiry date is within the limit.<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Be sure to check that the red handle is attached.<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Check that the gas cylinder is firmly tightened.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><b>Hammar M1 Model:<\/b><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Make sure that the red handle is attached.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><b>If YES is the answer to ALL these questions, then proceed to:<\/b><\/p>\n<p>7. When you insert the inflator body, make sure the gas cylinder is pointing upwards inside the bladder. The sealing ring can rest on the body&#8217;s rounded sealing surface.<\/p>\n<p>8. Make sure that the position of the hydrostatic valve in the replacement cap is pointing to the right, 90\u00b0 relative to the gas cylinder. Put the replacement cap in place on the body.<\/p>\n<p>9. First, press firmly on the inflator cap, and then turn the black locking ring clockwise until the locked position is reached.<\/p>\n<h2>FINAL CHECK<\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Make sure the cap has been locked on the inflator body properly by pulling the cap.<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">The locking ring should not be able to be turned counterclockwise by hand. Try to turn the locking ring to make sure it is properly locked.<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Inflate the Hammar A1\/M1 lifejacket through the oral tube to make sure it can inflate properly. Check that it stays inflated at least over one night.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2>PACKING<\/h2>\n<p>Before packing, deflate the lifejacket through the oral tube. Make sure that all residual air is pressed out from the bladder to assure the best activating conditions for the inflator and that it can be folded properly according to the manufacturer&#8217;s instruction. Make sure the lifejacket is dry before packing.<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\"  id=\"fl-accordion--label-3\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-controls=\"fl-accordion--panel-3\">A1 \/ M1 Periodic Service<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\" id=\"fl-accordion--icon-3\"  tabindex=\"0\"><i title=\"Expand\">Expand<\/i><\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<h2>A1 PERIODIC CHECK<\/h2>\n<ol>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Check that the indicator is green. ( \u2022 )<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Check that the expiry date is within the limit.<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Check that the red handle is attached.<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Check that the gas cylinder is firmly tightened by holding it through the lifejacket fabric.<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">To protect the sealing ring from damage that can affect the sealing function, always inspect the sealing ring for wear and tear.<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">To make sure the inflation is working properly, inflate the Hammar A1 lifejacket by using the oral tube. Be sure to check that it stays inflated over the night.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<h2>PACKING<\/h2>\n<p>Before packing, deflate the lifejacket through the oral tube. Make sure that all residual air is pressed out from the bladder so that it can be folded properly according to the manufacturer&#8217;s instruction. Make sure the lifejacket is dry before packing.<\/p>\n<h2>Check periodically<\/h2>\n<ol>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Check that the indicator is green. ( \u2022 )<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Check that the expiry date is within the limit.<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Check that the red handle is attached.<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Check that the gas cylinder is firmly tightened by holding it through the lifejacket fabric.<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">To protect the sealing ring from damage that can affect the sealing function, always inspect the sealing ring for wear and tear.<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">To make sure the inflation is working properly, inflate the Hammar A1 lifejacket by using the oral tube. Be sure to check that it stays inflated over the night.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<h2>Packing<\/h2>\n<p>Before packing, deflate the lifejacket through the oral tube. Make sure that all residual air is pressed out from the bladder so that it can be folded properly according to the manufacturer&#8217;s instruction. Make sure the lifejacket is dry before packing.<\/p>\n<h2>M1 PERIODIC CHECK<\/h2>\n<ol>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Make sure the red handle is attached.<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Check that the gas cylinder is firmly tightened. Do this by simply holding the gas cylinder through the lifejacket fabric.<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Make sure you always inspect the sealing ring for wear and tear that can affect the sealing function.<\/li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Inflate the lifejacket manually through the oral tube. Check that it stays inflated over one night.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<h3>\n\t\t\tFREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS\t<\/h3>\n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\"  id=\"fl-accordion--label-0\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-controls=\"fl-accordion--panel-0\">1. Where can I find an authorised service station?<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\" id=\"fl-accordion--icon-0\"  tabindex=\"0\"><i title=\"Expand\">Expand<\/i><\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\tPlease check with your lifejacket manufacturer:<br \/>\nAxis PFD\u00b4S Australia &#8211; <a href=\"http:\/\/www.axispfds.com.au\">www.axispfds.com.au<\/a><br \/>\nBaltic Safety Products AB &#8211;<a href=\"https:\/\/baltic.se\/\">www.baltic.se<\/a><br \/>\nCanepa &amp; Campi &#8211; <a href=\"https:\/\/canepaecampi.com\">www.canepaecampi.com<\/a><br \/>\nCertec &#8211; <a href=\"http:\/\/www.certec.fr\">www.certec.fr<\/a><br \/>\nCrewsaver &#8211; <a href=\"http:\/\/www.crewsaver.com\">www.crewsaver.com<\/a><br \/>\nHelly Hansen &#8211; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.hellyhansen.com\/lifejackets\">www.hellyhansen.com<\/a><br \/>\nInternational Safety Products Ltd. &#8211; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.oceansafety.com\/\">www.oceansafety.com<\/a><br \/>\nKRU &#8211; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.oceansafety.com\/\">www.oceansafety.com<\/a><br \/>\nMarinePool &#8211; <a href=\"http:\/\/www.marinepool.com\">www.marinepool.com<\/a><br \/>\nMesica Marine <a href=\"https:\/\/mesicamarine.com\/en\">www.mesicamarine.com\/<\/a><br \/>\nMullion Manufacturing Limited &#8211; <a href=\"http:\/\/mullion-pfd.com\/\">www.mullion-pfd.com\/<\/a><br \/>\nMustang Survival Corp. &#8211; <a href=\"http:\/\/www.mustangsurvival.com\">www.mustangsurvival.com<\/a><br \/>\nOcean Safety &#8211; <a href=\"https:\/\/oceansafety.com\/\">www.oceansafety.com<\/a><br \/>\nPakpoord Ou &#8211; <a href=\"http:\/\/www.marinepool.com\">www.marinepool.com<\/a><br \/>\nPlastimo S.A. &#8211; <a href=\"http:\/\/www.plastimo.com\">www.plastimo.com<\/a><br \/>\nPoseidon NZ &#8211; <a href=\"http:\/\/www.poseidonnz.com\">www.poseidonnz.com<\/a><br \/>\nSeawolf Marine &#8211; <a href=\"http:\/\/www.seawolf.co.kr\">www.seawolf.co.kr<\/a><br \/>\nSioen N.V &#8211; <a href=\"http:\/\/www.sioen.com\">www.sioen.com<\/a><br \/>\nSpinlock &#8211; <a href=\"http:\/\/www.spinlock.co.uk\">www.spinlock.co.uk<\/a><br \/>\nTakashina Life Preservers Co. Ltd. &#8211; <a href=\"http:\/\/www.tlpc.co.jp\">www.tlpc.co.jp<\/a><br \/>\nUrsuit &#8211; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ursuit.com\/en\/jackets\/life-jackets\">www.ursuit.com<\/a><br \/>\nVeleria San Giorgio S.R.L. &#8211; <a href=\"http:\/\/www.veleriasangiorgio.com\">www.veleriasangiorgio.com<\/a><br \/>\nViking Life-Saving Equipment &#8211; <a href=\"http:\/\/www.viking-life.com\">www.viking-life.com<\/a><br \/>\nRegatta &#8211; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.regatta.no\/en\/\">www.regatta.no<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\"  id=\"fl-accordion--label-1\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-controls=\"fl-accordion--panel-1\">2. There are no authorized service stations in my area. Who should I contact?<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\" id=\"fl-accordion--icon-1\"  tabindex=\"0\"><i title=\"Expand\">Expand<\/i><\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Please, contact the lifejacket manufacturer for advice. See above.<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\"  id=\"fl-accordion--label-2\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-controls=\"fl-accordion--panel-2\">3. I&#8217;m out at sea most of the time and with limited access to a service station. What should I do?<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\" id=\"fl-accordion--icon-2\"  tabindex=\"0\"><i title=\"Expand\">Expand<\/i><\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Make sure to always carry a Hammar Inflator Rearming Kit onboard and follow the step-by-step rearming instruction. Keep your rearming kit circulating and, under safe conditions, jump in the water to try your inflatable lifejacket out.<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\"  id=\"fl-accordion--label-3\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-controls=\"fl-accordion--panel-3\">4. I&#8217;m a recreational user, and in my country, we are advised to service the lifejacket every second year. Is that correct?<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\" id=\"fl-accordion--icon-3\"  tabindex=\"0\"><i title=\"Expand\">Expand<\/i><\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Self-service once a year and using an authorized service station every second year is a reasonable compromise.<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\"  id=\"fl-accordion--label-4\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-controls=\"fl-accordion--panel-4\">5. I don&#8217;t use my lifejacket regularly. How often do I have to service my lifejacket?<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\" id=\"fl-accordion--icon-4\"  tabindex=\"0\"><i title=\"Expand\">Expand<\/i><\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>All inflatable lifejackets must be serviced annually regardless of use.<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\"  id=\"fl-accordion--label-5\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-controls=\"fl-accordion--panel-5\">6. Can I clean my lifejacket?<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\" id=\"fl-accordion--icon-5\"  tabindex=\"0\"><i title=\"Expand\">Expand<\/i><\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>You must wash your lifejacket according to the instructions from the lifejacket manufacturer.<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li> The Hammar Inflator will withstand a normal rinse with the lifejacket hanging.<\/li>\n<li> For more thorough washing, always remove the inflator. After washing, let the lifejacket dry before rearming (see rearming instructions).<\/li>\n<li> Do not dry clean.<\/li>\n<li> When not in use, always store your lifejacket in a dry and ventilated space.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\"  id=\"fl-accordion--label-6\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-controls=\"fl-accordion--panel-6\">7. Can I replace my automatic inflator with a manual one?<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\" id=\"fl-accordion--icon-6\"  tabindex=\"0\"><i title=\"Expand\">Expand<\/i><\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>All Hammar Lifejacket Inflators share the same interface with the bladder. So yes, it is possible. Check with the lifejacket manufacturer to verify that the certification allows for conversion.<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\"  id=\"fl-accordion--label-7\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-controls=\"fl-accordion--panel-7\">8. Can I bring my Hammar inflator with me when flying?<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\" id=\"fl-accordion--icon-7\"  tabindex=\"0\"><i title=\"Expand\">Expand<\/i><\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>The Hammar inflator is not affected by the pressure differences created in the air.<\/p>\n<p>Whether or not you are allowed to bring it onto an aeroplane is up to the airline. Inflatable lifejackets are considered life-saving appliances, inflatable, and should generally not be an issue to bring onboard. There is an inflatable lifejacket stored under each seat of the aeroplane as demonstrated in the pre-flight safety demonstration.<\/p>\n<p>Check with your airline before flying and ask for their specific recommendations on how you may transport your inflatable life-saving appliance.<\/p>\n<h3>\n\t\t\tCAN\u00b4T FIND YOUR ANSWER?\t<\/h3>\n\t\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/contact-us\/\" target=\"_self\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tContact Us\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/a>\n\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Ursuit DSH Hydro 275N is a lightweight, comfortable automatic lifevest with an actual buoyancy of 320N. The lifevest has a Quick Burst \u2122 YKK zipper with a closed pattern (designed especially for Lifevests), and reflectors that go around the whole lifevest. User comfort is enhanced with a neoprene collar mesh triangle which prevents air buildup&#8230;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":9,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"footnotes":""},"class_list":["post-67","page","type-page","status-publish","hentry"],"acf":[],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v26.7 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/plugins\/seo\/ -->\n<title>Lifejacket Inflators - Hammar<\/title>\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"The heart of an inflatable lifejacket is the Inflator. Find out more about Inflators and how CM Hammar&#039;s solution may the choice for you.\" \/>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1\" \/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/lifejacket-inflators\/\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:locale\" content=\"en_US\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\" \/>\n<meta p